Description: I’m putting up for sale 5 of my Ibanez guitars. Check my other listings or the last picture. I got a little bit carried away with the gear acquisitions, so now will have to sell the ones that I don’t play. This listing is for Ibanez RG471AH in natural ash finish. It’s in very good condition. Has coil split switches, which give you 9 tone options total! Gibraltar standard bridge, strap locks, sharktooth inlays, Wizard III neck, made in Indonesia. It does show signs of use, light scratches here and there, and the area below pick ups has dirt rubbed into the grains. Discolored hardware. And there is a spot on the back of the neck. See pictures for yourself. Will need to be restrung definitely. Beautiful guitar, hard to find, and I believe it’s the only example on eBay at the moment, hate to let it go but I just have way too many guitars. Here’s some info from web: The RG471AH is an RG series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 2011. The RG471AH features an ash body bolted to a maple Wizard III neck with a 24-fret rosewood fingerboard with binding an sharktooth position markers. Components include Ibanez Infinity pickups with a pair of humbuckers flanking a single-coil and a Gibraltar Standard fixed bridge. US only. Will ship within 2 days of receiving payment. There are two shipping options and free local pick up if you are in NYC area.
Title: Ibanez RG471AH Natural Ash Shark tooth Inlays Wizard Neck Gibraltar Bridge Coil
